# 🔥 EnergyX — Notebook 04
## Combustion, Gas Turbines, Coal, Nuclear & Fuel Cells

```elixir
Mix.install([
  {:energyx, "~> 1.0"},
  {:kino, "~> 0.12"},
  {:kino_vega_lite, "~> 0.1"},
  {:vega_lite, "~> 0.1"}
])
alias VegaLite, as: Vl
```

---

## 1. Combustion Stoichiometry

```elixir
# Bituminous coal typical ultimate analysis (as-received, dry)
coal_props = EnergyX.Fossil.Coal.coal_properties()
IO.puts("Coal properties reference:")
Enum.each(coal_props, fn {grade, props} ->
  IO.puts("  #{grade}: LHV=#{props.lhv_mj_kg} MJ/kg, C=#{props.carbon_pct}%, Ash=#{props.ash_pct}%")
end)
```

```elixir
# User-defined fuel
c_input  = Kino.Input.number("Carbon fraction (mass %)",   default: 72.0)
h_input  = Kino.Input.number("Hydrogen fraction (mass %)", default: 4.5)
o_input  = Kino.Input.number("Oxygen fraction (mass %)",   default: 7.0)
s_input  = Kino.Input.number("Sulfur fraction (mass %)",   default: 2.0)
ea_input = Kino.Input.number("Excess air (%)",             default: 20.0)
Kino.Layout.grid([c_input, h_input, o_input, s_input, ea_input], columns: 3)
```

```elixir
c  = Kino.Input.read(c_input)  / 100.0
h  = Kino.Input.read(h_input)  / 100.0
o  = Kino.Input.read(o_input)  / 100.0
s  = Kino.Input.read(s_input)  / 100.0
ea = Kino.Input.read(ea_input)

afr_stoich = EnergyX.Fossil.Combustion.stoichiometric_afr(%{c: c, h: h, o: o, s: s})
hv         = EnergyX.Fossil.Combustion.heating_value(%{c: c, h: h, o: o, s: s})
flue       = EnergyX.Fossil.Combustion.flue_gas_composition(%{c: c, h: h, o: o, s: s, ea: ea})

IO.puts("""
Combustion Analysis:
  AFR (stoichiometric): #{afr_stoich.afr_stoich} kg_air/kg_fuel
  LHV: #{hv.lhv_kj_kg} kJ/kg | HHV: #{hv.hhv_kj_kg} kJ/kg
  CO₂ in flue gas (dry): #{flue.co2_pct}%
  O₂ in flue gas:        #{flue.o2_pct}%
  SO₂:                   #{flue.so2_pct}%
""")
```

---

## 2. Gas Turbine — Brayton Cycle

```elixir
rp_data =
  Enum.map(2..40, fn rp ->
    ideal  = EnergyX.Thermal.Thermodynamics.brayton_efficiency(%{pressure_ratio: rp * 1.0})
    actual = EnergyX.Fossil.NaturalGas.gas_turbine(%{
               pressure_ratio: rp * 1.0, t_inlet_c: 15.0,
               t_turbine_inlet_c: 1350.0, eta_comp: 0.87, eta_turb: 0.88})
    ccgt   = EnergyX.Fossil.NaturalGas.ccgt_efficiency(%{
               eta_gt: actual.eta_actual, eta_hrsg: 0.92, eta_steam: 0.35})
    %{"Pressure Ratio" => rp,
      "Ideal Brayton (%)"  => Float.round(ideal.eta_pct, 2),
      "Actual GT (%)"      => Float.round(actual.eta_actual * 100, 2),
      "CCGT (%)"           => Float.round(ccgt.eta_combined * 100, 2)}
  end)

Vl.new(width: 650, height: 360, title: "Gas Turbine & CCGT Efficiency vs Pressure Ratio")
|> Vl.data_from_values(rp_data)
|> Vl.transform(fold: ["Ideal Brayton (%)", "Actual GT (%)", "CCGT (%)"],
                as: ["Cycle", "Efficiency (%)"])
|> Vl.mark(:line, stroke_width: 2)
|> Vl.encode_field(:x, "Pressure Ratio", type: :quantitative)
|> Vl.encode_field(:y, "Efficiency (%)", type: :quantitative, scale: [domain: [0, 70]])
|> Vl.encode_field(:color, "Cycle", type: :nominal)
|> Kino.VegaLite.new()
```

