## 4. Nuclear Reactor — Four-Factor Formula

```elixir
IO.puts("Four-Factor Formula: k_eff = η · ε · p · f · P_NL")

eta_input = Kino.Input.number("η (reproduction factor)", default: 2.02)
eps_input = Kino.Input.number("ε (fast fission)",        default: 1.05)
p_input   = Kino.Input.number("p (resonance escape)",    default: 0.80)
f_input   = Kino.Input.number("f (thermal utilisation)", default: 0.71)
pnl_input = Kino.Input.number("P_NL (non-leakage)",      default: 0.97)
Kino.Layout.grid([eta_input, eps_input, p_input, f_input, pnl_input], columns: 3)
```

```elixir
ff = EnergyX.Nuclear.Advanced.four_factor_formula(%{
  eta: Kino.Input.read(eta_input),
  epsilon: Kino.Input.read(eps_input),
  p_res: Kino.Input.read(p_input),
  f: Kino.Input.read(f_input),
  p_nl: Kino.Input.read(pnl_input)
})

IO.puts("""
Reactor Criticality Analysis:
  k_∞ = #{ff.k_inf}
  k_eff = #{ff.k_eff}
  Reactivity ρ = #{ff.reactivity_pcm} pcm
  Status: #{ff.status}
""")

# Radioactive decay example — Cs-137
decay = EnergyX.Nuclear.radioactive_decay(%{n0: 1.0e12, half_life: 30.17, t: 100.0})
IO.puts("Cs-137 decay (t½=30.17 yr, t=100 yr):")
IO.puts("  Remaining fraction: #{Float.round(decay.fraction_left * 100, 3)}%")
IO.puts("  Half-lives elapsed: #{decay.half_lives_elapsed}")
```

